    <main>
        <h2>Our Computer System Landing Page</h2>
        <p>Welcome to the Monashee Co-op's IT infrastructure hub. This page provides a general overview of our server room and computer system setup, designed to support our cooperative’s operations efficiently and reliably. Prepared by Shanta McBain, IT Department.</p>

        <div class="features">
            <h3>1. Server Room Setup</h3>
            <p>Our server room is the backbone of Monashee Co-op’s digital operations, housing critical hardware in a rack-mounted configuration. Key components include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Server Rack</strong>: A 19-inch, 42U rack to accommodate current and future equipment. <a href="https://www.startech.com/en-ca/server-management/4postrack42u" target="_blank">Example: StarTech 42U Rack</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Servers</strong>: 1-2 rack-mounted servers (e.g., Dell PowerEdge R350) running a mix of Windows Server and Linux for file storage, applications, and virtualization.</li>
                <li><strong>Networking</strong>: A 24-port Gigabit switch (e.g., Cisco SG350) ensures robust connectivity across our systems.</li>
                <li><strong>Power & Cooling</strong>: A 1500VA UPS and portable AC unit maintain uptime and temperature control.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The setup is flexible, currently favoring a rolling rack for cost-efficiency, with plans to transition to a dedicated room as we grow.</p>
            <img src="https://blog.networkprofile.org/content/images/2020/01/2020-01-25-11.52.48.JPG" alt="Server Rack Example" width="500" height="600">
        </div>

        <div class="features">
            <h3>2. Workstations & Devices</h3>
            <p>Our computer system supports a diverse range of devices to meet staff and operational needs:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Windows Workstations</strong>: Desktops and laptops running Windows 10/11 for administrative tasks, equipped with Microsoft Office and co-op-specific software.</li>
                <li><strong>Linux Workstations</strong>: Select machines running Ubuntu or Fedora for technical staff, supporting development and system administration.</li>
                <li><strong>Laptops</strong>: A mix of Windows and Linux laptops for mobility, used by staff for remote work and on-site flexibility.</li>
                <li><strong>Phones</strong>: VoIP phones integrated with our network for internal and customer communication.</li>
                <li><strong>Square Till Setups</strong>: Point-of-sale systems using Square hardware, connected to our servers for transaction processing and inventory management.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This hybrid environment ensures compatibility and efficiency across all co-op functions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="features">
            <h3>3. System Goals</h3>
            <p>Our IT infrastructure is designed to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide reliable access to shared resources (files, applications, and tills).</li>
                <li>Support a growing workforce with scalable hardware and software solutions.</li>
                <li>Ensure security through regular updates, backups, and physical safeguards.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We aim to balance cost with capability, leveraging both new and used equipment where practical.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="features">
            <h3>4. Next Steps</h3>
            <p>To explore detailed plans or provide feedback, contact the IT department. Further documentation, including the full server room proposal, is available upon request.</p>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
